snippet.title: Freya Skye - golden boy
snippet.description:
Freya Skye "stardust" EP OUT NOW 

Listen/download here
Amazon: http://music.amazon.com/albums/B0GK5LXNPM?trackAsin=B0GK5HF392
Apple: https://apple.co/4q6KRvM
Itunes: https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/Title/1872542998?ls=1&app=itunes&at=1010lKkZ
Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/album/2HNjUP7VDUpyxQ2J3Cbch4
YouTube Music: https://music.youtube.com/playlist?list=OLAK5uy_lUnvU60mxdl8LaYe1G6axRe83BVASzkUs
 
D/P: Michel Borden

Subscribe to my YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/@iamfreyaskye 
Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/freyaskye
Follow me on Tiktok: https://tiktok.com/@freya

Lyrics to “golden boy” 

There was trail of destruction 
That led straight to you 
Ignored all the signs
That I wish weren’t true
You’re such a good actor
I guess you had me fooled
 
Guess I was convenient
When I was around
Cuz you love attention
The talk of the town
And I’d build you up
While you’d just tear me down
 
What’s done is done 
I’m on the other side now
 
So you can play the golden boy
And lose yourself in all the noise of
“You’re kind, and you’re so perfect” 
“I’d love to be your girlfriend”
You were lucky once
How’s life living on the surface?
 
We’d talk all the time
Now we don’t even speak 
I’m wide awake 
While you’re both still asleep 
You’re so unaffected 
By our history
 
But what’s done is done 
I’m on the other side now
 
So you can play the golden boy
And lose yourself in all the noise of
“You’re kind, and you’re so perfect” 
“I’d love to be your girlfriend”
You were lucky once
How’s life living on the surface?
 
You can really play the part
While you stay breaking all these hearts 
Oh “what’s it like to be his girlfriend”
Looks good but it’s a burden
You were lucky once
Have fun living on the surface
 
I’m thankful
You’re no longer wasting my time
I’m grateful I gave up
On reading your mind 
I know that it’s much better
Ending like this
Just one on your list 
Deceived and dismissed  
No I’m not alone being left in your mess 
It should bring me closure, or something I guess 
But all that I’m left with are unproven words 
That everyone heard, and what makes it worse
 
Is you just play the golden boy
And got so lost in all the noise of
“You’re kind, and you’re so perfect” 
“I’d love to be your girlfriend”
 
How’s life living on the surface?
You can really play the part
While you stay breaking all these hearts 
Oh “what’s it like to be his girlfriend”
Looks good but it’s a burden
You were lucky once
Have fun living on the surface

Music video by Freya Skye performing golden boy.© 2026 Hollywood Records, Inc.

snippet.title: The Equalizer 4: The Final Stand (2026) | Denzel Washington, Jason Statham | Concept Trailer
snippet.description:
#Equalizer4 #DenzelWashington #JasonStatham

Watch This The Equalizer 4: The Final Stand Fan Made Concept Trailer (2026)

After years of fighting crime and taking down villains, Robert McCall (Denzel Washington), finally gets to take a break, but at a price, as he discovers that the criminal network he's been dismantling over the years, has been intentionally leaving clues leading directly to him. Jason Statham joins the cast as Viktor Crane, a legendary "fixer" in the criminal underworld, known for solving problems with precision, just like McCall is known for solving them with the law. Viktor is the most deadly adversary Robert has ever had, because they are similar in their tactics, but unlike Robert, Viktor doesn't have morals; he's simply interested in being the best at what he does.

What will make the final stand so exciting is watching the top predator turn into prey when someone that's almost as skilled as he is, decides to put a permanent stop to the world's most famous vigilante. The action scenes will be career defining for both stars, as Washington and Statham go back and forth in a series of violent exchanges that will span the globe, with both men able to anticipate the other's next move, because they're both using the same tactics developed from their years of violence. We will also get to see McCall out of his element as Crane systematically takes out the people closest to him, before coming after him, which means that for the first time we've seen McCall defend himself instead of attacking, as he tries to protect the people he cares about, rather than trying to destroy those he sees as evil. Statham adds a level of depth to Viktor that we haven't seen before, as he's not driven by a desire to change the world, or greed, but by pride - he wants to prove himself as the best, and McCall represents the ultimate test, and if he declines this contract, it will be a sign that he admits defeat. As for Washington, he gives us his most emotional performance yet, as McCall comes to terms with the fact that he may be running out of time, and he begins to question whether all of the lives he's saved and all of the evil he's destroyed have really made a difference, and whether one man's battle against injustice ever really changes the balance of good vs evil, since evil always seems to regenerate faster than good. Overall, the film will explore themes of legacy and purpose as McCall confronts the reality that his methods of justice may have created more enemies than they eliminated, and that sometimes the greatest battles are the ones that don't result in victory. Fans of the series should expect long periods of suspenseful buildup, extreme hand-to-hand combat, and an ending that pays tribute to McCall's legacy, while also recognizing that some battles come to an end quietly, rather than with a victory.

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Highlander Highlander follows Connor MacLeod, an immortal warrior born in Scotland centuries ago, as he navigates a modern world while carrying the weight of countless lives, battles, and losses. Guided by his mentor Juan Sánchez-Villalobos Ramírez, Connor is forced to confront the true purpose of immortality as ancient rivalries resurface and The Gathering draws closer, pulling long-hidden warriors back into conflict. As past and present collide, Connor faces his most dangerous adversary in the relentless Kurgan, an immortal driven by conquest and domination. Set against a grounded, character-focused narrative, the story explores legacy, restraint, and the cost of survival across centuries, laying the foundation for a renewed mythos that honors the core of the original while reimagining its path forward for a new era.
